{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"a9e4d49c-604a-4d38-a0a9-cb519a7f8eb1","content":"Found **1 untestable static call** in your project:\n\n| File | Line | Call |\n|------|------|------|\n| `my_app/views.py` | 3 | `datetime.now()` |\n\n**Why it's problematic:** `datetime.now()` is a hard-coded static call that can't be easily mocked in tests, making time-dependent logic difficult to verify.\n\n**Recommended fix:** Use Django's `django.utils.timezone.now()` (which is easier to mock with `freezegun` or `unittest.mock.patch`), or inject a clock dependency:\n\n```python\nfrom django.utils import timezone\n\ndef index(request):\n    now = timezone.now()\n    return render(request, 'index.html', {'time': now})\n```\n\nThen in tests you can use `@freeze_time(\"2026-01-01\")` or `@mock.patch('django.utils.timezone.now')` to control the value.\n\nWould you like me to apply this fix?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"bdeb8d72-58b8-4168-bfc0-ed841f98f723","outputTokens":238,"requestId":"982B:1B0168:135631F:183C7F9:69FFF3B2"},"id":"44b3ce78-f500-4f2a-baf7-5d9b48a47f33","timestamp":"2026-05-10T02:55:52.721Z","parentId":"b0bae569-84b2-4ca5-a49f-dc0b4cdbe0cb"}
